Maruti Suzuki, Tata Motors Jump After Reporting Higher Sales

-- B y   A m e y a   K a r v e
-- 
2011-03-01T08:40:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-01/maruti-suzuki-tata-motors-jump-after-reporting-higher-sales.html
  Maruti Suzuki India Ltd . and  Tata
Motors Ltd . led gains among Indian automakers after the
companies reported higher sales last month.  Maruti Suzuki, India’s biggest carmaker, surged as much as
8.7 percent to 1,313 rupees before trading at 1,273.5 rupees at
2 p.m. in Mumbai. That was its steepest climb since May 2009.
Tata Motors, the owner of Jaguar Land Rover, was at 1,129 rupees
after earlier jumping as much as 9.9 percent to 1,190 rupees.  Maruti sold 111,645 vehicles in February, up 16 percent
from a year earlier, and Tata Motors’s sales for the month rose
12 percent to 77,543 vehicles, according to separate e-mailed
statements by the companies today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ameya Karve in Mumbai 
 akarve@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
 dboey@bloomberg.net . 